    introEn: "Spanish verbs reveal WHEN something happens through their ending – yesterday, now or tomorrow. You don't need to master every tense: a few are enough for travelling. The most important are the present, one past tense for telling stories and a simple future trick (ir a + infinitive). Here you'll watch them travel through the tenses with a single verb – tomar (to take).",
